This paper is about speech translation, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions the use of neural machine translation models, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of pre- and post-processing routines, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions the use of audio and subtitles, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
